Vice President Mike Pence visited Covenant Church in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, to discuss the aftermath of George Floyd's death and the ongoing protests. Pence emphasized the need for justice, condemned violence and looting, and expressed support for law enforcement while acknowledging the importance of addressing historic inequities in minority communities. He mentioned efforts to improve police training and standards, expand access to capital for African American businesses, and increase educational choice for minority families. Pence also highlighted the need to address healthcare disparities and expressed a commitment to working together with community leaders to make progress in these areas.